1 delinquency petition in the cour t . The minor's fitness to proceed may be raised by the
2 court before which the proceedings are pending or being held, or by motion of a party,
3 at any time during the proceeding.
4 2. If there is reason to doubt the minor's fitness to proceed, adjudication may not occur
5 until after a determination is made on the fitness of the minor to proceed in
6 accordance with this chapter.
7 27 - 20.5 - 04. Use of previous findings and records - Deflection .
8 A minor who is found to lack fitness to proceed due to previous judicial findings of lack of
9 fitness to proceed or considerations from school, medical, or other records within the last twelve
10 months may have the delinquency proceedings dismissed before a fitness to proceed
11 examination or remediation services are administered.
12 27 - 20.5 - 05. Due process .
13 1. If there is reason to doubt the minor's fitness to proceed , adjudication may not occur
14 until after a determination is made except the filing of a delinquency petition, until
15 counsel is appointed and notified in accordance with section 27 - 20.2 - 12 and the minor
16 is found to have the mental capacity to proceed.
17 2. After the case proceeds to adjudication or the minor is found to lack fitness to proceed,
18 the court shall order all of the reports that are submitted under this chapter to be
19 closed to the public. The court may order the reports be opened for inspection only:
20 a. For further fitness to proceed or criminal responsibility examination;
21 b. For statistical analysis;
22 c. If the records are considered to be necessary to assist in mental health treatment
23 ordered ;
24 d. For data gathering;
25 e. For scientific study or other legitimate research;
26 f. To the state's attorney or minor's counsel for the purpose of an active court case
27 subject to the prior evaluation; and
28 g. To an employee or agent of the division of juvenile services or the department of
29 health and human services, if necessary in the performance of the employee's or
30 agent's duty.
